---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About · System Journal">
	<main
		class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-[700px] flex-grow flex-col gap-section-gap px-md py-section-gap md:px-gutter"
	>
		<!-- Header -->
		<header class="flex flex-col gap-stack-lg">
			<h1
				class="font-headline-lg-mobile text-headline-lg-mobile text-on-surface md:font-headline-lg md:text-headline-lg"
			>
				About the Journal
			</h1>
			<div class="h-1 w-16 rounded-full bg-primary"></div>
		</header>

		<!-- Bio -->
		<section class="flex flex-col gap-stack-md">
			<h2 class="font-headline-md text-headline-md text-on-surface">The Author</h2>
			<p class="font-body-lg text-body-lg text-on-surface-variant">
				I am a systems engineer specializing in low-level architecture, distributed systems, and
				performance optimization. For over a decade, I've navigated the complexities of
				high-throughput environments, debugging race conditions at 3 AM, and architecting scalable
				backends that handle millions of concurrent connections.
			</p>
			<p class="font-body-lg text-body-lg text-on-surface-variant">
				My approach to engineering is rooted in pragmatism and a deep respect for foundational
				computer science principles. I believe that elegant code is not just about aesthetics, but
				about maintainability, predictability, and efficiency at the hardware level.
			</p>
		</section>

		<!-- Purpose -->
		<section
			class="flex flex-col gap-stack-md rounded-xl border border-outline-variant bg-surface-container-low p-stack-lg"
		>
			<h2 class="font-headline-md text-headline-md text-on-surface">The Purpose</h2>
			<p class="font-body-md text-body-md text-on-surface-variant">
				System Journal exists as a repository of hard-won knowledge. It's a space where I document
				technical debt stories, architectural wins, and the subtle nuances of systems programming
				that often go undocumented. The goal is to share these insights with fellow engineers who
				value rigorous technical discourse over superficial tutorials.
			</p>
			<ul
				class="mt-stack-sm flex list-inside list-disc flex-col gap-stack-sm font-body-md text-body-md text-on-surface-variant"
			>
				<li>Deep dives into concurrency models and synchronization primitives.</li>
				<li>Post-mortems of system failures and the lessons learned.</li>
				<li>Explorations of memory management and cache optimization techniques.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<!-- Confidentiality -->
		<section
			class="flex flex-col gap-stack-md rounded-r-xl border-l-4 border-primary bg-surface-container-lowest p-stack-lg"
		>
			<div class="flex items-center gap-stack-sm text-primary">
				<span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-variation-settings: 'FILL' 1;">security</span>
				<h2 class="font-headline-md text-headline-md">Principles of Engineering Integrity</h2>
			</div>
			<p class="font-body-md text-body-md text-on-surface-variant">
				Confidentiality is paramount. All proprietary details, architectures, and specific business
				logic related to my employers or clients are strictly obfuscated. The scenarios discussed
				here are abstracted to focus on the underlying engineering principles and architectural
				patterns, ensuring absolute privacy while maintaining technical accuracy.
			</p>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
